## Workflow: Research Processing

**Purpose**: Process external sources into standardized research format.

**When to Use**: Adding new research from URLs, files, or chat sessions.

### Input Types

**URL Processing:**
- Fetch web content
- Convert to standardized markdown
- Extract key insights and frameworks
- Add citation-ready quotes

**File Processing:**
- Process PDFs, docs, reports
- Extract text and key concepts
- Create structured source document

**Chat Session Processing:**
- Capture current conversation insights
- Extract strategic decisions discussed
- Create reusable research artifact

### Source Document Format

```markdown
---
title: "[Source Title]"
source_type: "website|pdf|report|chat-session|framework"
source_url: "[URL if applicable]"
date_added: "[YYYY-MM-DD]"
date_expires: "[YYYY-MM-DD]"
topic: "[strategic-topic]"
relevance_tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
data_confidence: "high|medium|low"
---

# [Source Title]

**Source**: [Author/Organization]
**Original URL/Location**: [If applicable]
**Date Published**: [Original date]
**Data Confidence**: [High/Medium/Low with justification]

## Key Insights

[Strategic insights that directly inform decisions]

## Strategic Applications

[How this applies to decision-making context]

## Key Quotes/Data Points

> "Verbatim quote for citation"
> — Author, Source (Date)

## Related Internal Context

[Links to relevant meetings, roadmap items, other sources]

## Notes

[Thoughts, connections to other research]
```

### Output Location
- `datasets/research/sources/{topic}/{filename}.md`

