## Source Quality Standards

### Data Confidence Levels

| Level | Criteria |
|-------|----------|
| High | Authoritative source, recent data, verified methodology |
| Medium | Reliable source but some limitations (age, scope) |
| Low | Useful insights but significant limitations |

### Citation Requirements

- Preserve verbatim quotes (5-25 words) for key claims
- Include source attribution
- Format for easy citation in memos
- Track original source URL/location

### Expiry Management

- Set appropriate expiry based on content type
- Flag sources approaching expiry
- Recommend refresh for stale data
- Archive sources no longer relevant
